⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Hardy–Weinberg
node POP · POP · ⟦Hardy–Weinberg:POP:6ef3aa⟧

WHO   — Hardy–Weinberg — the no-evolution baseline · p²+2pq+q²
WHAT  — The null hypothesis of evolution: the frequencies a population WOULD hold if nothing pushed on it.
WHERE — POP · Population Dynamics  Framework inputs: ecology, epidemiology, population genetics; Asimov's Foundation; verified & cited  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Life Science)
WHY   — Because to measure evolution you need the picture of no evolution — and this is it.
HOW   — By predicting genotype frequencies from allele frequencies under random mating, reached in one generation.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the still point: what the gene pool looks like when nothing is acting on it. Evolution is everything that makes me move.

